A diesel-laden tanker has fallen just a few metres beyond Otedola Bridge as travellers navigate entry into Ogun State end of the Lagos-Ibadan Expressway. As reported by the Traffic Response Squad via its Twitter handle @rrslagos767, traffic build-up has extended to Ojota on account of the accident. “Motorists are advised to drive with caution. Emergency responders are making efforts to remove the fallen tanker,” RRS tweeted. See the video of the accident, tweeted by @SubDeliveryZone: